@node main "Frequently Asked Questions (We wish!)"

                          C r e A m   F A Q s (?)
                          =======================

  To start with the name, it is short for  CREative AMigites, which is what
we hope to be in the  future.  The  name  was  invented  by  @{"Won-Tolla" link wontolla}, who
actually @{"thought of it" link oldname} several years before the group got started.

                             @{"How did it start?" link history}
                          @{"Who are we? (pen names)" link pennames}
                         @{"Who ARE we? (real names¹)" link realnames}
                               @{"«Pen names»?" link pennameexp}
                               @{"What is this?" link whatitis}
                         @{"Where do we go from here?" link future}

                           @{"A note on birthdates" link birthdates}

                  [Editorial comments in [] by @{"Won-Tolla" link wontolla}]

¹and a limerick as well!
@endnode

@node oldname "Is this guy psychic or what?"

   Yes, as I just said the name is older than the group,  but I'm not real-
ly trying  to tell you  I thought of  it AS A  NAME FOR THIS  GROUP several
years  before it got started! What I mean is it's a couple of years since I
first thought something like "Wouldn't it be something to gather a group of
creative amigites?  I could call it, err, CreAm!"  The current group is not
exactly what I had envisioned back then, but it's a beginning...

@endnode

@node birthdates "Why don't we just say how old we are?"

  As you will notice when you start  looking  through this file, one of the
things you're told about  the  members  is  their birthdates. We originally
used just their ages, but then I (Won-Tolla) realised that information like 
that becomes outdated very quickly ("Sure, he says he's 17, but WHEN did he
say that?"), so we decided to use birthdates  instead; that way you can al-
ways calculate how old we are  right  now.  (And  besides  there's always a
chance that someone out there will send us birthday cards!)

  By the way, the dates are  given  in  Norwegian  format  (day-month-year)
rather than what seems to be the  Swedish  standard  (year-day-month), even
for the Swedes. Hey, I'm the one  writing  this file, I've got to have some
privileges, you know! :-)

@endnode

@node history "A short stroll down Memory Lane (no, not the RAM bus!)"
                             How did it start?
                             -----------------

  In the late summer of '94, our  @{"leader-by-default"link leaderbydefault}  (later  to be known as
@{"Scarycat" link scarycat}) inserted an ad in various Scandinavian Amiga mags [Well, two that
I know of actually...]. It  got  answered  by  various people, some of whom
seemed to lose interest before  we  got  anything  done.  At least Scarycat
claims he never received anything  from  some of the original "members", or
they started taking too long to answer his letters.

  That's it really... Unless you want to see @{"ScaryCat's version" link origin}.

@endnode
  
