@node pennameexp "'Pen names'?"
                  What's this business about "pen names"?
                  ---------------------------------------

  One of my (Won-Tolla's) little pet peeves. @{"Scarycat" link scarycat}, our esteemed @{"leader-" link leaderbydefault}
@{"by-default" link leaderbydefault}, insists on using the more traditional  term "code names", but I
insist that this term suggests that  we  are using the names to conceal out
@{"true identities" link realnames}, as if we've got something to hide. Well, we've GOT nothing
to hide (Maybe except for our  lousy  skills  ;-)),  so I suggested using a
different term. In the beginning I  tried  introducing  the term "aliases",
but have now settled for "pen names" instead,  hoping it will catch on bet-
ter than "aliases".
  [Of course,  Amigites rarely  use  pens,  but  "mouse names" or "keyboard
names" is a bit too weird even for us...]

@endnode
  
@node whatitis  "Let me explain..."
                               What is this?
                               -------------

  Well, it's a slide show with a fancy (?) intro and some home-made picture
transition effects we  hope  you  will  like.  The  title was thought up by
@{"Scarycat" link scarycat}, who thought he should be  the  first to name a production because
he is the leader. [I will probably  be  next  because I've got imagination!
;-) -- WT]
  Later we may come up with something a bit  more fancy (and CREative), but
at the time being we are a lot of  artists  with  just one musician and one
programmer (Well, there are several members  who claim to program, but only
one has had the guts to prove it so far! :-))
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  By the way, the program goes through the pictures twice, first at its own
pace, then you set the pace. So you can stare at (or rather through) Scary-
cat's stereograms for a couple of  minutes  if  you like. If you want to go
"manual" before reaching the end of the first round, just press the Esc key
until the music starts to fade. When  the  new music starts, you can change
pictures by clicking the mouse (but you  won't get my intermission message,
and you don't get a second look!).

@endnode
  
@node future "The future isn't what it used to be... but then again, it never was!"
                         Where do we go from here?
                         -------------------------

  Well, apart from being the title of  a  song  it's also the question with
the vaguest answer.  After taking nearly a year  to get a little slide show
together, we hope of course  to  move  on  to bigger and better things (and
get them done a bit faster too! :-)),  but that's all in the future. (Where
else? :-))

  And who knows,  once all our artists have learned to draw behind the tool
box we may even start exploring overscan mode! :-)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

  [A little note from the editor:  Our  next  project  will probably have a
Guide file enclosed too (if space  permits),  and in connection with that I
would like to point out that this  file  was created "manually" - if anyone
reading this has one of those  programs  for editing this kind of file (and
it's PD or shareware!),I would like to @{"get a copy" link wontollahome}!]

@endnode

@node arcade "Who is Arcade?"

  Mattias "Arcade" Bengtsson  (29.08.78)  is  the group's only (active) mu-
sician so far. He wrote both the tracks  - the first one, which he for some
reason refers to as "that superb  tune  which should be repeating itself in
your head by now" [At  least  it  keeps  repeating  in  MY head, but that's
mainly because I ran the program fifty times to test it during development!
-- WT] is called is called "Look out", the other "New Hope".
  He also drew the CreAm logo in  the intro,  and even  found  time between
tunes to contribute a couple of pictures:  his own logo and a couple called
@{"Lady Death" link arcpics} and  @{"Spt" link arcpics}  (whatever  that  means,  it's  supposed  to  be a long
distance shot of a spaceship that presumably  didn't stay long enough for a
closeup).

                            @{"Where does he live?" link arcadehome}
                 @{"What does that stupid name stand for?" link arcadename} ;-)
                     @{"What has he got?" link arcadeware} (@{"hardware" link nosoft})
                             @{"What does he do?" link arcadework}

@endnode

@node arcpics "A note about Arcade's pictures"

