  To repeat his own words again [Well,  I've  got nothing better to do with
them haven't I? -- WT], Mattias  (or  Arcade  if  you  prefer) lives in the
beautiful town of Trollhättan [To  venture  a guess, the name seems to mean
something like "troll's hood". Oh,  and  the ä is  pronounced "eh".], about
nine metric miles from Gothenburg [Where @{"Mr. Fish" link fish} lives, if he's still with
the group...]. Trollhättan is best  known  as the place where Saab cars are
made.

@endnode

@node arcadename  "What does that stupid name stand for?"

  Contrary to popular  belief  [Well,  I  used  to  believe it...] the name
Arcade has nothing to do with a  certain  X-Men villain, but it may have at
least a little to do with arcade games. Back in his C64 days when he got on 
the highscore table of a game, he  would  enter his initials as ARC because
his proper initials JMB didn't  look  very  interesting!  The initials were
supposed to stand for Actually  Really  Cool,  and later developed into the
full name ARCADE. [Suggestions for what the rest of the name may be an abb-
reviation for are welcome! -- WT]

@endnode

@node arcadeware "What has Arcade got?"

  Arcade does not like to  rattle  of  all  he's  got  because  he does not
believe in the "whoever has the most  toys  when they die wins" philosophy,
but after the usual rounds of  torture  he admitted being in the possession
of an A500 with a 400M hard  drive  [Drat,  that  means he wins...! -- Won-
Tolla's 212M drive], a MIDI interface and  a poly 800 keyboard that is "old
as hell, even older than Won-Tolla,  and  he's  really old". [Wouldn't that
mean it isn't MIDI compatible?]

@endnode

@node arcadework "What does Arcade do?"

  Arcade is one of Marvel's numerous crazy  assassins whose specialty is to
make his assignments into a  game...  Whoops,  sorry,  wrong character! OUR
Arcade writes music (with Protracker  "because  he  likes it so much"), and
whenever he's not being bossed around by ScaryCat or not  working (huh?) on
another tune for the group's  next  release,  he  just takes it easy. [Wise
fellow!] He liks to draw and  write  (and  animate,  according  to SC), amd
whenever he manages to tear himself away from the Amiga, he loves to PARTY!

@endnode
  
