@node paddingtonname "What does that stupid name stand for?"
  
  "It's an tribute to one of the  best  role-models  in  the world. I mean,
have you ever read a book where @{"Paddington" link teddy} punched the light out on anyone,
has he ever been mean to anyone on purpose? And he's so cute too. But to be
honest, I just picked out a name that wasn't taken :=)"

[Sure, but how does that fit in with all  the swords and devils and burning
crosses you draw? -- WT]

@endnode

@node teddy "A book about Paddington? What the hell are you talking about?"

  And for those who really didn't  know,  the original Paddington being re-
ferred to here is a teddy bear who  got  that  name because he was found at
the Paddington railway station in  London,  which in turn got its name from
the district it's located in.  And  if  you  think I'm going to stop there,
you're wrong - I happen to have  a  placename  dictionary  which informs me
that the name originally means  "Padda's  Farm",  so there must have been a
farm there once, associated with (but not  owned by) one Mr. (?) Padda, who
presumably didn't know that his (?) name means "the Newt" in modern Norweg-
ian!!
  Alright, HERE I'm going to stop. But if  you find that OUR Paddington has
drawn a lot of little green reptiles  for  our next production, you'll know
the reason! ;-)

@endnode
  
