@node scarycatname "What does that stupid name stand for?"
  
  Well, here's one I know for a change! :-) That's because I am the one who
made it up for him. Because  his  initials  spell  BOO,  I got the idea for
something "scary", and  a  scarycat  is  supposed  to  be the opposite of a
scarEDYcat.

  (Of course, if you  insert his pen name  between the middle and last name
the way it's done in the credits and some places in this file, his initials
suddenly become BOSO, which is NOT the same as a "bozo"! (It's only the im-
pression you get...) ;-)

@endnode
  
@node scarycatware "What has Scarycat got?"
  
  Apart from a big ego ;-), Scarycat used  to have an Amiga 500+, a printer
and a @{"sampler" link voice}, but recently (Spring '95)  he bought a second-hand 2000 that
came with a hard disk (to  be  replaced  with  a  bigger one), a genlock, a
monitor and another printer (which he either has sold or is trying to sell,
depending on when you read this!),  and  he's waiting impatiently for Escom
to start bringing out the new 1200s...

@endnode

