@node 57 "What's so special about that date then?"

  Right, born in -57, that makes me  the  oldest member and also a bit spe-
cial in two other ways. Of  late  I  have  developed  the  habit of telling
people who inquire about my age that  I  am  of the same vintage as @{"Ernie's" link ernie}
DeSoto!
  1957 was also the year when King Haakon  the 7th died (which is why I can
always remember what year it  happened!).  He  died much later in the year,
though, so you could say that I have just barely lived under three kings to
date (1995).

@endnode

@node ernie "Who the hell is Ernie?"

  Either you are one of those people  who  klick on everything in sight, or
you gave up reading newspaper  comic  strips  when  they started shrinking.
Surely you've heard of Ernie Floyd from  Bayonne (?) and his trusty (rusty)
57 DeSoto? If not, just pick up some  newspaper  and a magnifying glass and
look around a bit...

  This may be as good a place as any to mention that I'm also interested in
comics, so if we ever get a plot together  and get the artists to cooperate
it's quite possible that one of our future  publications will be a comic on
disk (or maybe even on paper...).

  (By the way, in case it should interest  anyone, my favourite Ernie strip
(so far!) is the one where Spencer  has  found  a new way to get money from
adults - by telling them he wants to be just like them when he grows up. It
works fine until he tries it on  Uncle  Sid,  and if you don't remember the
punchline you've got one more excuse for @{"writing me" link wontollahome}!)

@endnode

