@node wontollaname "What does that stupid name stand for?"
  
  Well, what do you know? I know this one  too! :-) I got the name from the
Jungle Book (click @{"here" link junglequote} for details).  The  reason I picked this particular
name (rather than Hathi, that  was  my  name  as  a "wolf cub" ages ago) is
very simple really.  One day a couple  of years back I got in touch with an
amigite who called  (and for  all I  know  is  still calling) himself "Lone
Wolf" because he did not belong  to  any  group.  I found that I was in the
same situation, but I couldn't exactly steal the name, so I started looking
for something similar.  Then I  remembered Won-tolla, a  name which  freely
translated  can mean  "lone wolf".  It's  a bit paradoxal  to use it within
a group, but it's all I've got, and at  least it's  better than  some names
I could (but won't) mention...
  
@endnode
  
@node junglequote "Short excerpt from a classic."
  
   The following is quoted from  the  Kipling  story "Red Dog":
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   They heard tired feet  on the rocks, and a gaunt wolf, streaked with red
on his flanks, his right  fore-paw useless,  and his  jaws white with foam,
flung himself into the circle and lay gasping at Mowgli's feet.
   "Good hunting! Under whose Headship?" said Phao gravely.
   "Good hunting! Won-tolla am  I," was the  answer. He meant that he was a
solitary wolf,  fending for himself,  his mate and  his cubs in some lonely
lair, as do many wolves  in the south. Won-tolla means an Outlier - one who
lies out from any Pack.  Then he panted, and they could see his heart-beats
shake him backward and forward.
   "What moves?"  said Phao,  for that  is the question all the Jungle asks
after the _pheeal_ cries.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Well, if you want to know what was moving in the Jungle that day and how
my namesake got  into such a state, I recommend a trip to the library where
you can no doubt  find a copy of The Second Jungle Book, which is where the
rest of the story can  be found.  But if  all you  want to know is why this
miserable wolf is my namesake, just click Retrace and read on.
@endnode

@node wontollaware "What has Won-Tolla got?"
  
  Won-Tolla is somewhere in  the  middle  as  far as being well-equipped is
concerned. Since the  beginning  of  the  computer  age,  he's gone through
several  different computers, of  which he still  has an Apple ][+, a C128,
his first Amiga  (a 500 version 1.2)  and the  one he's currently using, an
Amiga 500+ with a hard disk that keeps threatening  to run over, extra disk
drive and RAM (total 12 MB), a sampler that doesn't work and a streamer and
a Zip drive that do.  He's also kept his first printer which he got for the
Apple (mostly because noone else wants it), but also has a (relatively) new
and much better bubble jet printer. As soon as he can afford to get a phone
he'll (probably) also get a modem.
  
@endnode
  
@node wontollawork "What does Won-tolla do?"
  Well, well! What does he NOT do?  Won-Tolla  programs  a lot - he started
with various Basics (and a little  6502)  on his older machines, "advanced"
to AmigaBasic, and is now mostly  converted to Amos. He's got DICE and True
Basic installed on the hard disk as  well,  but  hasn't really got very far
with either as there are so many  other  and  more fun things to do with an
Amiga than learning a new programming language...
  He also likes to play with Imagine  (as previously  mentioned, two of his
contributions to this slide  show  are  test  renders)  and experiment with
stills and animations  in  DeluxePaint,  and  recently started on his first
MovieSetter creation (probably only to be released in Norway, so don't hold
your breath!). Also plays a bit with  OctaMED,  but  isn't too good at this
either.
  When he's not trying to be creative,  he spends far too much time playing
computer games, quarreling with  Scarycat  ;-)  and playing PBM games. He's
also currently looking for a  job after his boss went  and died on him last
year...

Oh yes,  he also  writes the  occasional limerick, as seen on the @{"real name" link realnames}
page!  (They usually  rhyme better, too!  Come on,  how many  words can YOU
think of that rhyme on "Amigites" or "demo"?)
@endnode
  
