                                             WAS STARTED....

                                             By ScaryCat - 1995

  Well boys and  girls,  Ragnar  "Won-Tolla"  Fyri has  written  over seven
hundred lines in this file, so  I  guess  I'll  have to spit in a couple of
sentences too. [With a bit of help from the editor, whose English and logic
is better than his. (Well, he said so himself! At least about the English.)
-- WT] As the acting leder of CREative  AMigites I try as hard as  possible
to pull the strings and keep the members in the group from  collecting each
others' heads... Well, usually they  are  very nice too each other, but I'd
rather keep a certain control over them.
  (Well I haven't had a difficult job so far since the other members do not
seem to want to contact each other  personally...  besides going through me
at first...) [It's just much easier  to  write to him when he's supposed to
keep in touch with everyone anyway! -- WT]

  Anyway...  whether you want it or not, I will tell you how I got the idea
of  starting CreAm.  I've been into computers  since 1992 and the first two
years I only  played games. But then  I  thought, "There MUST be more to it
than only  being able to play  games!?",  and it was then I started drawing
pictures in Deluxe Paint 3. Now I am using Deluxe Paint 4 [But he ain't got
no manual... -- WT], which  is  my  favourite   program.  HEY!!!  I DO HAVE
OTHERS TOO!!! Such as TRUE BRILLIANCE,  PROFESSIONAL DRAW, IMAGINE 2.0, and
some others which I don't bother  to    mention.  [Of course he has to have
more than one program to name  one  of  them  his  favourite! See my remark
about logic in the opening! -- WT]

  Anyway... in the spring of 1994 I  tried  to  join the group BEHIND BARS;
at that time I  called myself ASAP.  Silly name, ehh!!??  [Stop stealing my
lines! -- WT]
  Anyway, for about 2 months I lived  in  the belief that I finally had be-
come something, but then one day I  got  this  letter from the leader of BB
saying that I never had been a  member,  and he kicked my ass so  to speak.
So, Mr. Criminalis/BEHIND BARS, if you ever get the chance to  read this, I
hope you can see that I ain't as  stupid  as  you wrote the last time [He's
worse! :-) -- WT]. Now you've got COMPETITION!!!!!!!!!!!!!! GOOD LUCK!!!!!!
(Actually I think it IS time for you to go BEHIND BARS... ha!!)

  YES....YES..I  SHALL  CONTINUE!!!!!!!!  As  you probably have reckoned, I
went mad and  my  nice  ego  said  to  me  (translated  from  Norwegian  of
course..): "Make your own group, and  show  those  assholes that you can do
just as well as them." [In  other  words,  if  you  can't find a group that
wants you, start one that does!  :-)  --  WT]  That was IT. I put an adver-
tisement in 3 computer magazines,  and  a lot [Well, half a dozen... -- WT]
of Amiga enthusiasts answered it. Yup!!! That's how CreAm was started.
  The first to answer was Ragnar "Won Tolla"  Fyri... [Editor takes a bow.]
so because he also is the oldest of  us...he  has been the one who also has
answered most  and   therefore  become  my  closest  right-handed member in
CreAm. [Actually I'm  part  ambidextrous...  Oh,  he means right-hand man I
guess... -- WT]
  If anyone out there with an AMIGA reads this [Let's face it, you'd have a
tough time reading it WITHOUT an Amiga! -- WT], then you are all welcome to
@{"write to me" link scarycathome} if you have questions [Like "Why bother?" :-) --WT], and if you
are lucky then perhaps I  will answer YOU!!!  [Or @{"write ME" link wontollahome}, I try to answer
EVERYONE. -- WT]
  AND IT WOULD ALSO BE COOL IF ANY  OF  YOU  WHO  SEE THIS FIRST SLIDE SHOW
FROM CreAm COULD @{"WRITE TO ME" link scarycathome} AND TELL US WHAT YOU THINK OF IT. [Not if they
are honest! :-) -- WT]

  PS: If you don't write English [but can read it well enough to understand
this... -- WT] you can @{"write" link scarycathome} to me in French.  But PLEASE don't @{"write" link scarycathome} to ME
in GERMAN, since I will not be able to understand any of it. [Jawohl! --WT]
Errr... @{"write" link scarycathome} only short  FRENCH letters  since I only have had one year of
French at school.  [He means  letters in French,  but you could always @{"send" link scarycathome}
him a "French letter" too -  he's  got  other  "amigas" than his Amiga, you
know! -- WT]


                            Ha det!
                            Bye!
                            Au Revoir!


             MAY THE AMIGA LIVE FOREVER!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

                                --- Bård "ScaryCat" Olsen ---

