@node nosoft "Screw the hardware, I want to know about your software!"

  As you will find when you click the "What has he got?" button to the left
of the one you just clicked to get here (unless you're >browsing of course)
this file limits itself to listing the hardware used by members.
  There is a simple reason for this:  Anyone  who  has had an Amiga (or any
other computer) for some time will  have  accumulated hundreds of programs,
or at least far too many to list.  [When  I  found that one of the members,
who shall remain anonymous, had  included  such trivialities as Relokick on
his list, I realised I was on the wrong  track.] We could of course include
a list of the programs each member  uses  most frequently, but that is sort
of implicit in the "What does he do?" entry,  and we're trying to avoid too
much redundant information here...

@endnode

@node finalnode "A little extra for browsers only!"

  Congratulations, you have found the secret message! This node can only be
reached by browsing because it has no links from anywhere else in the file.

  Of course you may regret finding it once you have read my Pun Of The Day.
You see, I wanted to give a friend of mine something special for his birth-
day, so I sent him  a strip-o-gram  (like a  singing telegram,  only with a
stripper instead of a singer).  Unfortunately, my  friend was not  home, so
the girl came back marked "Return to sender, undress anon"!

